stack.authentication.AuthenticationConfi.name: stack.authentication.AuthenticationConfig
stack.authentication.AuthenticationConfi.description:
The AuthenticationConfig is a configuration implementation leveraged
by the authentication module. The AuthenticationConfig implementation
provides configuration settings to the Authentication module.

stack.authentication.AuthenticationContr.name: stack.authentication.AuthenticationController
stack.authentication.AuthenticationContr.description:
The AuthenticationController aids in the protecting and locking down
of authenticated routes. Unauthorized requests are redirected to a
configurable unauthenticated route.

stack.authentication.AuthenticationModel.name: stack.authentication.AuthenticationModel
stack.authentication.AuthenticationModel.description:
The AuthenticationModel houses CRUD-based methods used to
authenticate users.

stack.authentication.AuthenticationServi.name: stack.authentication.AuthenticationService
stack.authentication.AuthenticationServi.description:
The AuthenticationService wraps the AuthenticationModel and houses a
collection of methods used to manage the authentication of users.

stack.authentication.ProtectResolver.name: stack.authentication.ProtectResolver
stack.authentication.ProtectResolver.description:
The ProtectResolver service should only be applied to routes that require
authentication. This service examines the authentication status of the
current user. If a user is authenticated they are allowed to view the
route. If a user is unauthenticated they are directed back to a configured
unauthenticated route.

stack.authentication.PublicResolver.name: stack.authentication.PublicResolver
stack.authentication.PublicResolver.description:
The PublicResolver service should only be applied to publicly-facing routes.
This service examines and returns the authentication status of the current user.
The user status is then leveraged to show/hide areas within globally-accessible
components such as the header or sidebar that require authentication to be seen.

stack.authentication.name: stack.authentication
stack.authentication.description: Module definition houses the authentication feature.

stack.develop.DevelopConfig.name: stack.develop.DevelopConfig
stack.develop.DevelopConfig.description:
The DevelopConfig provides adopting implementations with a 'develop'
configuration option. Depending upon the implementation, it is sometimes
useful to understand whether or not the application is in a 'develop' or
'production' mode. DevelopConfig provides the .setDevelop(flag) method and
should be configured within the compiled app.html page.

See /clientserver/views/app.html for example.

stack.i18n.stackLocalize.name: stack.i18n.stackLocalize
stack.i18n.stackLocalize.description:
The Localize directive takes a token and returns a translated
string using the Translation service and injects the translated
string into the DOM element.

stack.i18n.localize.name: stack.i18n.localize
stack.i18n.localize.description:
The Localize filter takes a token and returns a translated
string using the Translation service. This method is more
processor-intensive given the number of times a filter is
called and should be used sparingly. If possible, leverage
the stackLocalize directive instead.

stack.i18n.TranslationConfig.name: stack.i18n.TranslationConfig
stack.i18n.TranslationConfig.description:
The TranslationConfig is a configuration implementation leveraged
by the i18n implementation.

stack.i18n.TranslationModel.name: stack.i18n.TranslationModel
stack.i18n.TranslationModel.description:
The TranslationModel houses CRUD-based methods used to
retrieve and manage localized strings.

stack.i18n.TranslationResolver.name: stack.i18n.TranslationResolver
stack.i18n.TranslationResolver.description:
The TranslationResolver service loads a map of strings based
upon the locale reported by the browser.

stack.i18n.TranslationService.name: stack.i18n.TranslationService
stack.i18n.TranslationService.description:
The TranslationService wraps the TranslationModel and provides
convenience methods for managing the the translation of strings
based upon different locales.

stack.i18n.name: stack.i18n
stack.i18n.description: Module definition houses the i18n feature.

stack.location.LocationService.name: stack.location.LocationService
stack.location.LocationService.description:
The LocationService extends the angular $location service
and the ui router $state service. It provides additional
url parsing methods and location functionality.

stack.location.name: stack.location
stack.location.description: Module definition houses the location feature.

stack.page-loader.stackPageLoader.name: stack.page-loader.stackPageLoader
stack.page-loader.stackPageLoader.description:
The PageLoader directive provides a spinning loading icon
as well as a container overlay that the covers underlying
DOM elements.

stack.page-loader.name: stack.page-loader
stack.page-loader.description: Module definition houses the PageLoader feature.

stack.reveal.stackReveal.name: stack.reveal.stackReveal
stack.reveal.stackReveal.description:
The Reveal directive prevents UI flicker from happening
when an application is first loaded. This implementation
is different then using ng-cloak. The ng-clock directive
will prevent the angular brackets from rendering to end
users. The Reveal directive prevents a flicker caused
by css and js resources from loading at different times.

stack.reveal.name: stack.reveal
stack.reveal.description: Module definition houses the reveal feature.

stack.name: stack
stack.description:
Module definition houses collection of stack assets.
Stack assets consist of implementations that are
generic in nature and can be used across multiple
applications.

templates.name: templates
templates.description:
The templates module houses all of the application's templates
using the $templateCache service. The $templateCache service is
leveraged to reduce the number of http requests this application
must make when retrieving templates. If a template is stored in
the $templateCache the application will not make a request for
the template in question.

HeaderController.description:

Header.name: Header
Header.description: The Header directive houses the application header implementation.
example:
<uhg-header
        brand-link="login"                       // Route to link.
        authenticated="true"                     // Boolean flag that controls rendering of login/logout links.
        authenticated-route="about"              // Route to redirect to on successful login.
        unauthenticated-route="about"            // Route to redirect to on unsuccessful login.
        logo-path="/path/to/image.png">          // Path to header logo.
    </uhg-header>

        items="[]">              // Array of navigation objects.
    </uhg-list-navigation>
